		<hr size="1">Ummm, re-read what she said.  She is correct and she is not saying a lvl 1 caster has the same amount of mana as a lvl 50 caster.</P><P>The total amount of mana you can have is calculated on the fly so to speak.  Yes it is a function of your lvl but it is not fixed.  If you Int changes the total amount of mana you can have changes (dynamicaly).</P><P>Here is the formula for wizards... arghhh I can't find the link that has the equation but there are a few mana calculators on-line.  There is one here (Everlore) under Magic.</P><P>So to beat a dead horse with a stick a lvl 10 wizard will have the same amount of Mana at lvl 10 with an int of 140 regardless of what his int was while he was leveling.  And if this wizard was given a nice +5 int ring his Mana total would increase as soon as she put on the ring (she would have to med to get it however, the cap is raised not the current amount).</P><P>Cheers.<BR>Seeryin and Azzara on Drinal<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
