		<hr size="1">Your mana pool isn't set in stone. I explain:</P><P>Formula for amount of mana pre-50, for int up to 200:</P><P>(((int/5)+2)*level)+mana items = mana pool</P><P>That means your mana is determined as your int changes. When you ding, your mana isn't locked in for that level - your mana pool just increases because you're multipling by level+1 instead of your old level. </P><P>Or, in other words - a lack of +int items won't have any affect on your amount of mana at higher levels. <br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
