		<hr size="1">Mana calculators aren't all that convenient when you're at the Bazaar doing some comparison shopping, so here's another way to look at it**:</P><P>At level  5, +1 INT = +3 mana<BR>At level 10, +1 INT = +4 mana<BR>At level 15, +1 INT = +5 mana<BR>At level 20, +1 INT = +6 mana<BR>At level 25, +1 INT = +7 mana<BR>At level 30, +1 INT = +8 mana</P><P>and so on.  So when you're comparing +INT items vs. +mana items, at higher levels an item will have to have pretty high +mana to beat out a +INT item.</P><P>*based on the formula above<BR>**for INT less than 200<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
