		<hr size="1">didnt the soft cap get changed to 250 or 255 now with PoP?</P><P>and to help a bit with the question about INT vs Mana+</P><P>pre mid 30s you should be as much Mana+ as you can with some ok amount of INT, say in the 130-150 range for INT.</P><P>post mid 30s you should start swaping that old mana+ gear for INT gear to get over 200.</P><P>then late 50s or so you should start swapping that out for the higher end INT and Mana+ gear out there.  there are some items with +10INT and +100mana so that would be FAR better then just a +10int, but most of those are no drop or questable items for 50+ game.</P><P>my necro did not up his INT over 200 until 34th and as soon as i spent the coin in the bazaar and returned to my hunting grounds i could tell a HUGE differance between my old mana+ gear with under 200INT vs the new gear (got rid of most of my mana+ items, but not all) with 200+ int the killing was much safer and faster as i ran out of mana a lot slower then before.  therefor my mana pool was drasticaly increased in that fassion.</P><P><hr><font style=font-size:8pt color=yellow>*Worlds worst speller*<BR><font color=yellow><BR>"For those who believe, then no proof is needed.  For those who are skeptics, then no proof will suffice."<font color=00FFFF><BR>"Pigs get fat, but Hogs get slaughtered and VI is a big HOG."<BR><font color=yellow> "So, reading some of my posts is sort of like having sex in your parents house???"  Dr. Zin</P><P></font><BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
